  "body": "I am forking a node using `yarn hardhat node --fork https://astar-mainnet.g.alchemy.com/v2/<api_key>` but it's giving me this error:\r\n```\r\nError HH604: Error running JSON-RPC server: Invalid JSON-RPC response's result.\r\n\r\nErrors: Invalid value null supplied to : RpcBlockWithTransactions | null/transactions: RpcTransaction Array/0: RpcTransaction/accessList: Array<{ address: DATA, storageKeys: Array<DATA> | null }> | undefined, Invalid value null supplied to : RpcBlockWithTransactions | null/transactions: RpcTransaction Array/1: RpcTransaction/accessList: Array<{ address: DATA, storageKeys: Array<DATA> | null }> | undefined, Invalid value null supplied to : RpcBlockWithTransactions | null/transactions: RpcTransaction Array/2: RpcTransaction/accessList: Array<{ address: DATA, storageKeys: Array<DATA> | null }> | undefined, Invalid value null supplied to : RpcBlockWithTransactions | null/transactions: RpcTransaction Array/5: RpcTransaction/accessList: Array<{ address: DATA, storageKeys: Array<DATA> | null }> | undefined\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe node is working correctly as I am able to query the node using the `curl` command. \r\n\r\nSometimes even the `yarn hardhat node` works and sometimes doesn't work. \r\n\r\nThis is very strange for me as I have used hardhat on my machine but I haven't run into such a problem.\r\n\r\nSimilar issue: https://stackoverflow.com/questions/69659558/error-hh604-error-running-json-rpc-server-error0308010cdigital-envelope-rout\r\n\r\nMy machine specs:\r\nOS: Ubuntu 22.04\r\nNode: v16.16.0 \r\nHardhat: 2.11.2",
